In this part, you perform three administrative tasks &ndash; create the organization, add a user account, and configure the Windows workstation to connect to Chef Automate as that user.

An organization enables you to group related projects and provide scope for authorization rules. User accounts enable end users to access Chef Automate through its web interface or from the command line.

Here's what you'll do:

1. [Connect to the Windows workstation](#step1)
1. [Log in to the Chef Automate web interface](#step2)
1. [Add a user](#step3)
1. [Sign out of the Chef Automate web interface](#step4)
1. [Update your Chef Automate user with an SSH public key](#step5)
1. [Connect the Chef Automate CLI to the Chef Automate server](#step6)
1. [Set your Git identity](#step7)

