## 3. Add a user

Now you'll add a user.

Select **Organizations** from the drop-down menu in the upper right corner.

![](automate/wf-orgs.png)

Select the **Users** tab.

![](automate/wf-users-tab.png)

Click **+ New User**, then fill in the fields. The screen image below is an example. You can specify your real info if you prefer.

Leave the **Enter SSH Public Key** field blank &ndash; you'll set that up in the next part.

In practice, you would determine the appropriate [roles and permissions](https://docs.chef.io/delivery_users_and_roles.html#roles-and-permissions) for your user. For now, select all roles.

![](automate/wf-add-user.png)

When you're done, click **Save & Close**.

[COMMENT] Do not modify the `builder` account. Chef Automate requires these settings to enable build nodes to perform jobs.

